Test: connect to backend socket and close immediately with zero bytes sent.

Backend log:
[backend] started. real uid=0 effective uid=0
[backend] runtime check: effective UID = 0
[backend] listening on /tmp/authsvc.sock
[backend] frontend connected
[backend] recv: Success

Note: recv() returned 0 (clean EOF, not a true error), but errno was stale
at that point since recv() only sets errno on an actual failure (-1). The
program's n <= 0 check still correctly treats this as "no valid data" and
exits safely without crashing or hanging - but the message text itself is
misleading. This is a minor observation worth discussing re: error handling
correctness in the report
